results.wikipedia_summary: Chrysococcyx is a genus of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family. The scientific name Chrysococcyx is Greek for gold cuckoo (χρυσός,κούκος) Some authorities split the principally Australo-Papuan taxa into the genus Chalcites.
